# RAG System

Local semantic search over research literature via the `r2` CLI.

**Usage:** `r2 rag <command>`

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `search QUERY [-n N] [--citekey KEY]` | Retrieve relevant chunks with citations |
| `query QUERY [-n N] [-p TEMPLATE] [--citekey KEY]` | Retrieve + formatted prompt for synthesis |
| `self-query QUERY [-n N] [--citekey KEY]` | Over-retrieve + Self-RAG instructions (LLM grades relevance) |
| `deep-query QUERY [-s '["q1","q2"]'] [-n N]` | Decompose query into sub-questions, retrieve per sub-question |
| `index [--force] [--source bib\|dir\|all]` | Index PDFs into vector store |
| `stats` | Index statistics |
| `remove CITEKEY` | Remove a paper from the index |
| `lit-search QUERY [--focus broad\|top_journals\|classical\|recent] [-n N]` | Search Semantic Scholar + OpenAlex + Scopus |
| `lit-paper PAPER_ID` | Get paper details from Semantic Scholar |
| `lit-citations PAPER_ID [-n N]` | Forward citations |
| `lit-references PAPER_ID [-n N]` | Backward citations |
| `lit-deep-research QUERY [--focus F] [--n-external N] [--n-local N]` | Combined local RAG + external search |
| `lit-download IDENTIFIER [--type doi\|pmid\|title]` | Download PDF (Sci-Hub) + add to Zotero + index |
| `lit-download-batch 'JSON_ARRAY' [--auto-index]` | Batch download multiple papers |
| `lit-save-report QUERY --file report.md` | Save a literature review report |

- Save analyses to `library/` with descriptive filenames.
- Cite as `(Author Year, pp. X-Y)` from chunk metadata.
- Run `r2 rag index` before searching if new PDFs were added.
